{"type":"text","timestamp":1782540024351,"sessionID":"ses_0f8601eedffeolXZZg1RrCEXUr","part":{"id":"prt_f07a9eea4001QidSPDRMha6NZM","messageID":"msg_f07a9e3850014t1ylj2Ecazjlq","sessionID":"ses_0f8601eedffeolXZZg1RrCEXUr","type":"text","text":"Implemented the batch-1 phase-02 repository/session foundation and updated the authority rows for just the requested groups.\n\n**What Changed**\n- Expanded `entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/data/content/home_content_repository.cj`\n  - Brought the restaurant seed list up to full source parity: 16 restaurants.\n  - Added a source-aligned `getRestaurantFromName()` lookup.\n  - Kept `getRestaurantByName()` as a compatibility alias for current callers.\n- Tightened `entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/data/session/session_repository.cj`\n  - Added `setRestaurant()` / `getSavedRestaurantName()` to mirror source repository semantics.\n  - Snapshot selected restaurant menu items with zero quantity on selection.\n  - Made favourites mutate the shared list on like/unlike.\n  - Kept shared cart/favourite/selection state in one singleton repository for later phases.\n- Added focused phase test file `entry/src/test/cangjie/phase02_repository_contract_test.cj`\n  - Covers full restaurant seed exposure\n  - Exact restaurant lookup\n  - Selected restaurant to saved-name/menu snapshot propagation\n  - Like/unlike shared favourite mutations\n  - Cart seed retention\n\n**Authority Updates**\nUpdated `translation-inputs/source-coverage-matrix.json/md` for the requested batch groups only:\n- Closed real repository/session rows as `implemented`\n- Closed shared-state rows as `implemented-simplified` where the source used `Flow` but the target currently uses synchronous shared-state reads\n- Closed source-analysis false positives as `not-applicable`\n- Closed Android/Hilt lifecycle rows as `platform-replaced`\n\nKey rows updated included:\n- `FoodikeApp.kt` application/bootstrap rows\n- `FakeData.kt` batch rows\n- `HomeRepositoryImpl.kt` rows\n- `LoginRepositoryImpl.kt` rows\n- `UserDataRepositoryImpl.kt` rows\n- `AppModule.kt` rows\n\nI did not modify platform capability authority because the current phase capability checklist already had `runtime-permissions` and `background-and-platform-components` resolved, and the existing authority entries already matched that resolution.\n\n**Verification**\nOne bounded test reproduction was run:\n- `cjpm test` in `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/test/cangjie`\n\nResult:\n- Blocked by existing test package wiring, not by the new repository code.\n- Error: root package imports `kit.AbilityKit`, `kit.ArkUI`, and `ohos.resource`, but those dependencies are not visible to the test package through the current `cjpm.toml` setup.\n\nI recorded that exact blocker in the affected matrix rows as `harness-blocked` evidence.\n\nChanged files:\n- `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/data/content/home_content_repository.cj`: expanded source-parity catalogue and added source-aligned name lookup\n- `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/data/session/session_repository.cj`: aligned selected-restaurant, menu snapshot, favourites, and shared session semantics\n- `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/test/cangjie/phase02_repository_contract_test.cj`: added focused repository contract tests for this batch\n- `translation-inputs/source-coverage-matrix.json`: updated batch feature rows with status, endpoints, parity, and verification evidence\n- `translation-inputs/source-coverage-matrix.md`: synced from authority patch tool\n\nCommands run:\n- `cjpm test`\n- `python D:\\X2Cangjie\\X2Cangjie\\scripts\\shared\\source_coverage\\patch_authority.py --kind matrix --authority D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\source-coverage-matrix.json --patch C:\\Users\\Sieger\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\opencode\\phase02-batch1-matrix-patch.json --markdown D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\source-coverage-matrix.md --plan-json D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\plan.json --target-project D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\Foodike-Harmony`\n\nBuild result:\n- NOT RUN for full phase build\n- Test reproduction blocked: `cjpm test` in `entry/src/test/cangjie` fails due to missing test-visible package wiring for `kit.AbilityKit`, `kit.ArkUI`, and `ohos.resource`\n\nPlan changes:\n- none\n\nDeferred issues:\n- Test harness blocker for phase-02 focused tests: `entry/src/test/cangjie/cjpm.toml` / root package dependency visibility prevents `cjpm test` from compiling target imports used by the app package\n- Observable `Flow` semantics in login/user-data repositories are currently represented as shared synchronous state reads/writes at route boundaries; this was recorded as `implemented-simplified` where appropriate\n\nNext recommended action:\n- Continue phase-02 batch 2/3, or if you want stronger verification first, do one focused harness-repair session for the `entry/src/test/cangjie` package wiring so the new phase-02 tests can actually run.","time":{"start":1782540005028,"end":1782540024350}}}
